                                                                                                                                                            <div class="content-item bd-bot exercise-list-start">
                                    <h2 class="title-content">How to Put in Your Workout Split</h2>
                                    <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Biceps curls specifically target your biceps brachii. These consist of two muscle heads at the front of your upper arm. The dumbbell biceps curl involves elbow flexion and extension. These are the primary movements performed by your biceps.</span></p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">There are several options for incorporating them into your workout routine. For example, on a strength-focused day, prioritize working your biceps alongside opposite muscle groups to manage fatigue effectively. A good example would be a tricep pushdown.</span></p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Begin with compound pull exercises like rows or pull-ups. Follow with push movements like cable flies or chest presses using heavier weights. Then, alternate between isolation exercises targeting opposing muscle groups, like dumbbell biceps curls and triceps extensions. </span></p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Ensure adequate rest between sets of two to three minutes to maintain intensity and optimize muscle recovery. </span></p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">To increase muscle mass, add dumbbell bicep curls into your back and biceps day or pull day. They make an excellent accessory exercise for your heavy back workouts. Perform them after compound exercises like lat pulldowns, and single-arm rows. </span></p><p><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC8372753/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Split workouts and full-body routines</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> have been proven equally effective for muscle growth. In both routines, volume, also known as the amount of work done, needs to be equal. </span></p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">You can also dedicate an entire day to training your arms with biceps and triceps exercises only. Dumbbell curls are also great for full-body workouts, especially if you're </span><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC8449772/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener"><span style="font-weight: 400;">short on time</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> or aiming to improve performance efficiently.</span></p>                                                                    </div>
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        </div>
